<% content_for :xml_import do %>
<% #========================================================================= %>
<h1>XML import</h1>

<p>
  XML file projects and tasks are mapped to TrackRecord projects and tasks as
  follows:
</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    Any tasks with non-zero work time assigned are included.
  </li>
  <li>
    TrackRecord task names are generated from the name of each XML file task,
    with the name of its most immediate grouping parent summary added as a
    prefix.
  </li>
  <li>
    Assigned work time in the XML data is converted to TrackRecord project
    durations in hours, mathematically rounded to two decimal places if need
    be.
  </li>
  <li>
    Task codes are created from the current date and the task ID, this being
    typically directly related to position in which the task is listed in most
    graphical project plan editors.
  </li>
  <li>
    Tasks are imported "flat" since TrackRecord does not support hierarchical
    task structures.
  </li>
</ul>
<% #========================================================================= %>
<% end %>
